class loading process
         when JRE executing any byte code that time it will take 4 blockes of memory form the RAM
         inside static pool area it will take one dedicated area for the class, class static area.
         inside that csa alll the sataic variable willl be stored and value will be their default value
         it will store all he static intialixers and the static method address and their method signature.
         now it will execute all the static intializers from top  to bottom before executing the main method.
         if all the static insitializers is executed then class loading process is completed.then main method will store inside the stack area.

